    Introduction

    In this Lab Step, you will build a custom Docker image which contains a simple FLASK based web application. The custom Docker image will later be deployed into the Kubernetes cluster. Before performing the deployment within the cluster, you'll be shown how to create a new namespace resource and how to set it as the default namespace into which the remaining deployment takes place.

    Instructions  

    1. Within the Explorer view, navigate to and expand the lab/code/App/lab-code/flaskapp folder. This folder contains the following files:

    • Dockerfile
    • main.py

    Note: If the Explorer view hasn't yet loaded with the labs project (source code), add the following path to the current URL and reload the web page: /#/cloudacademy

    Open both files within the editor by double clicking on each of them. Review both files to understand their design.

    2. Within the Explorer view right-click over the lab/code/App/lab-code/flaskapp folder and then select the Open in Terminal menu option:

    3. A new terminal session is presented in the bottom pane. List the contents of the flaskapp directory. In the terminal execute the following command:

    ls -la

    4. Perform a docker build to create a custom docker image. In the terminal execute the following command:

    docker build -t cloudacademydevops/flaskapp .

    5. Check to see the presence of the newly built docker image with the tag cloudacademydevops/flaskapp:latest. In the terminal execute the following command:

    docker images 

    6. Create a custom cloudacademy namespace within the Kubernetes cluster. In the terminal execute the following command:

    kubectl create ns cloudacademy

    7. Swap into the new cloudacademy namespace. In the terminal execute the following command:

    kubectl config set-context --current --namespace=cloudacademy

     

    Summary

    In this Lab Step, you built a custom Docker image and then created a new namespace resource and set it as the default namespace into which the remaining deployment will take place.
